<topic id="ch_css_pseudo_classes_and_pseudo_elements">
    <title>CSS Pseudo-Classes and Pseudo-Elements</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>CSS<indexterm>pseudo classes</indexterm><indexterm>pseudo
          elements</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <body>
    <p>These keywords may be appended to the last sequence of simple selectors in a selector. It is
      possible to use one or more keywords in a single simple selector.</p>
    <section id="section_nwh_dmc_n1c">
      <title>Pseudo-Classes</title>
      <p>Each of these keywords specifies a special state of the selected element(s).</p>
      <p id="p_wtv_dgk_54b">The following table summarizes the pseudo-classes supported by <ph
          keyref="product"/>:<table id="table_nnv_mpt_cbb" frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
          <tgroup cols="4">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="2.25*"/>
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="9.01*"/>
            <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="3.14*"/>
            <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4" colwidth="1*" align="center"/>
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry>Pattern</entry>
                <entry>Meaning</entry>
                <entry>Described in section</entry>
                <entry>CSS level</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry>E:root</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, root of the document.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:first-child</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, first child of its parent.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>2</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:last-child</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, last child of its parent.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:first-of-type</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, first sibling of its type.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:last-of-type</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, last sibling of its type.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:only-of-type</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, only sibling of its type.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:only-child</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, only child of its parent.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:nth-child(n)</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, the n-th child of its parent.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:nth-of-type(n)</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element, the n-th sibling of its type.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:empty</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element that has no children (including text
                  nodes).</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#structural-pseudos"
                    format="html" scope="external">Structural pseudo-classes</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:lang(c)</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element in (human) language "c" (the document
                  language specifies how the language is determined).</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#lang-pseudo" format="html"
                    scope="external">The :lang() pseudo-class </xref></entry>
                <entry>2</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E:has(rs1)</entry>
                <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element that has a relative element that
                  matches the rs1 selector (as one of its children), when evaluated with E as the
                    <xref href="https://drafts.csswg.org/selectors/#relative-selector" format="html"
                    scope="external">anchor element</xref>.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://drafts.csswg.org/selectors/#relational" format="html"
                    scope="external">The :has() relational pseudo-class</xref></entry>
                <entry>4</entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table></p>
    </section>
    <section id="section_npt_jmc_n1c">
      <title>Pseudo-Elements</title>
      <p>Each of these keywords lets you style a specific part of the selected element(s).</p>
      <p>The following table summarizes the pseudo-elements supported by <ph keyref="product"
          />:<table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" id="table_bzz_kmc_n1c">
          <tgroup cols="4">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="2.25*"/>
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="9.01*"/>
            <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="3.14*"/>
            <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4" colwidth="1*" align="center"/>
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry>Pattern</entry>
                <entry>Meaning</entry>
                <entry>Described in section</entry>
                <entry>CSS level</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry>E::first-letter</entry>
                <entry>The first formatted letter of an <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#first-letter" format="html"
                    scope="external">The ::first-letter pseudo-element</xref></entry>
                <entry>1</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E::before</entry>
                <entry>Generated content before an <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#gen-content" format="html"
                    scope="external">The ::before pseudo-element</xref></entry>
                <entry>2</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E::after(n)</entry>
                <entry>Generated content after an <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element. Setting a
                  value of 1 creates a normal <codeph>:before</codeph>. A higher value means the
                  generated content is further from the element.</entry>
                <entry><xref
                    href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/ch_advanced_styling_multiple_before_and_after_pseudo_elements.html"
                    format="html" scope="external">The ::after(n) pseudo-element</xref></entry>
                <entry/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E::after</entry>
                <entry>Generated content after an <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#gen-content" format="html"
                    scope="external">The ::after pseudo-element</xref></entry>
                <entry>2</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E::before(n)</entry>
                <entry>Generated content before an <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element. Setting a
                  value of 1 creates a normal <codeph>:before</codeph>. A higher value means the
                  generated content is further from the element. </entry>
                <entry><xref
                    href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/ch_advanced_styling_multiple_before_and_after_pseudo_elements.html"
                    format="html" scope="external">The ::before(n) pseudo-element</xref></entry>
                <entry/>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>E::marker</entry>
                <entry>Generated by list items to represent the item’s marker (the bullet or number
                  identifying each item). <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> should include <codeph>display:
                    list-item</codeph>.</entry>
                <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-lists-3/#marker-pseudo" format="html"
                    scope="external">The ::marker pseudo-element</xref></entry>
                <entry>3</entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table></p>
    </section>
